WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:03.837
-NARRATOR:<i> Previously on</i> Boston Legal...
-You wanted to see me, Shirley?

00:03.920 --> 00:06.965
I'm very sorry,
but you won't be making partner.

00:07.048 --> 00:08.591
-(shouts)
-(all gasp)

00:08.675 --> 00:13.388
Jerry Espenson has been suffering
needlessly his entire life.

00:13.471 --> 00:15.849
Now he has a chance
to find a measure of peace.

00:15.932 --> 00:17.225
That's justice, Shirley.

00:17.308 --> 00:19.227
To friendship, my colleague.

00:20.687 --> 00:22.522
Right on my balcony?

00:23.398 --> 00:25.400
I don't want you on my balc--

00:25.483 --> 00:29.279
On... on any balcony, alone,
with that man.

00:29.529 --> 00:30.363
Okay.

00:31.406 --> 00:33.575
("'Til Your Fool Comes Home" playing)

00:34.701 --> 00:37.120
<i>-♪ Does temptation have you led astray? ♪</i>
-(elevator bell dings)

00:37.495 --> 00:38.580
Mornin'.

00:38.663 --> 00:41.041
<i>♪ Or countin' every day ♪</i>

00:41.124 --> 00:42.083
Hello!

00:44.335 --> 00:45.336
Family good?

00:47.630 --> 00:48.923
How about those Sox?

00:49.758 --> 00:52.927
<i>♪ To be alone</i>
<i>'Til your fool come home ♪</i>

00:54.846 --> 00:55.930
(sighs)

00:59.851 --> 01:01.061
Knock, knock.

01:02.270 --> 01:05.148
Jerry. (chuckles) Always a surprise.

01:05.482 --> 01:06.316
Shirley.

01:07.192 --> 01:12.322
First, I bear no ill will towards you
for totally screwing me out of partner.

01:12.781 --> 01:14.783
Thank you, and, uh...

01:15.158 --> 01:18.328
no hard feelings here
for you trying to slit my throat.

01:18.411 --> 01:20.580
(sighs) I'm very embarrassed over that.

01:20.663 --> 01:21.790
Don't beat yourself up.

01:23.792 --> 01:25.376
Wha... what's on your mind, Jerry?

01:27.796 --> 01:29.005
I want my job back.

01:31.716 --> 01:35.345
I built myself a nice little practice.
Here's a list of clients.

01:35.428 --> 01:37.472
-Many are blue-chip.
-SHIRLEY: Uh...

01:38.098 --> 01:42.060
Having succeeded
in building your own firm,

01:42.143 --> 01:43.520
why would you wanna come back?

01:44.145 --> 01:45.480
I miss the camaraderie.

01:45.563 --> 01:47.857
(scoffs) Jerry, you never spoke to anyone.

01:47.941 --> 01:50.026
I've improved in that department.

01:51.152 --> 01:52.737
Wha... what is it really, Jerry?

01:52.821 --> 01:57.700
(exhales deeply)
Well, last week, I had a case.

01:57.784 --> 02:01.579
Against Clarence Bell, actually,
a lovely man who works here.

02:02.163 --> 02:04.624
I was rather ugly in the trial, cutthroat.

02:05.250 --> 02:06.584
I've become more and more aware

02:06.668 --> 02:10.505
that's what you must be sometimes
in order to win cases, which I can accept.

02:11.089 --> 02:14.175
But you have to be that way far too often

02:14.259 --> 02:17.137
in order to compete in the marketplace,

02:17.220 --> 02:20.765
whether it's poaching clients
or beating up vendors.

02:21.432 --> 02:24.269
It's a very cruel world out there.

02:24.811 --> 02:25.854
I hadn't noticed.

02:25.937 --> 02:29.357
I don't want to be that way.
It's not who I am.

02:33.361 --> 02:36.990
I'll tell you what,
I will think about this.

02:37.073 --> 02:40.660
Any request this outrageous
deserves attention.

02:41.327 --> 02:44.497
But I do have a rule of thumb
when I hire people.

02:45.540 --> 02:48.501
I need to be convinced
they could be happy here.

02:48.585 --> 02:50.962
Oh, I could be. Shirley, I assure you.

02:51.045 --> 02:53.464
Just the thought of getting
to come back here again

02:53.548 --> 02:54.674
puts a song in my heart.

02:54.757 --> 02:57.010
I actually walk about
singing it in my head.

02:57.594 --> 02:59.095
You... you sing a song in your head?

02:59.179 --> 03:00.597
(chuckles) Yes.

03:01.681 --> 03:03.683
-Could you hum a few bars?
-(chuckles)

03:04.350 --> 03:05.185
Very good.

03:05.268 --> 03:08.188
No, really,
I... I would like to hear the song.

03:09.522 --> 03:10.815
Well...

03:11.566 --> 03:12.775
Okay.

