<i>♪ Boom, boom, boom ♪</i>

03:51.105 --> 03:54.400
On what grounds
were you arrested, Mr. Kallah?

03:54.484 --> 03:57.070
I was suspected of having ties
to Al-Qaeda, which is ridiculous.

03:57.820 --> 04:00.365
I'm assuming
you're not an American citizen.

04:00.448 --> 04:02.033
-I'm British.
-Commie.

04:03.743 --> 04:05.536
My sister is an American citizen
through marriage.

04:05.620 --> 04:08.248
-I'm applying for citizenship.
-Are you on a no-flying list?

04:08.957 --> 04:12.126
I have been. Went to rehab.
They love me now.

04:12.210 --> 04:15.171
Why were you in Afghanistan
in the first place?

04:15.255 --> 04:16.881
I was there on a humanitarian effort,

04:16.965 --> 04:19.759
bringing food, medical supplies
to some impoverished villages.

04:19.842 --> 04:21.761
I was arrested
by US intelligence officers.

04:22.136 --> 04:23.388
And sent to Guantanamo.

04:24.889 --> 04:25.932
For two years.

04:28.101 --> 04:29.269
Who won the Super Bowl?

04:30.520 --> 04:32.355
It'll be on the test.
I'm just trying to help, son.

04:32.855 --> 04:35.275
Mr. Kallah, you're a Harvard-educated man,

04:35.358 --> 04:37.527
presumably, well-informed.

04:37.610 --> 04:40.113
If you've so much as bothered
to read the newspapers,

04:40.196 --> 04:42.323
which not everybody does, I grant you,

04:42.407 --> 04:45.159
it can interfere with leadership skills.

04:45.243 --> 04:47.704
You know, uh, suing for abuse
at Guantanamo

04:47.787 --> 04:49.080
is next to impossible.

04:49.163 --> 04:51.457
-Which is why I've come to you.
-Commie.

04:53.042 --> 04:55.128
I was tortured by agents
of the United States.

04:55.211 --> 04:57.171
I should get to sue the United States.

04:57.255 --> 04:59.215
I don't know
what tribe you're from, sport.

04:59.299 --> 05:00.675
But this is America.

05:00.758 --> 05:04.178
Human rights are so yesterday here.
Get with the program.

05:07.390 --> 05:08.308
What?

05:08.391 --> 05:11.728
Mr. Kallah, you can thank Denny Crane.
He's just persuaded me to take your case.

05:25.616 --> 05:26.743
Have you lost your mind?

05:26.826 --> 05:28.995
More times than I care to mention, Judge.

05:29.078 --> 05:31.205
And it seems like each time
with a different woman.

05:31.289 --> 05:32.457
Are you free for lunch?

05:33.708 --> 05:37.628
Mr. Shore, it would not be wise
to make sexual advances.

05:37.712 --> 05:39.047
I tend to accept them.

05:40.173 --> 05:41.883
Can we turn to the case?

05:43.426 --> 05:45.136
I've completely forgotten what it's about.

05:45.762 --> 05:49.140
Your Honor, perhaps
you could refresh me over lunch.

05:49.640 --> 05:52.685
It's about you suing the government
for Guantanamo abuses,

05:52.769 --> 05:56.105
bringing it in state court, no less,
instead of federal, where it belongs.

05:56.189 --> 05:58.649
And the courts have ruled
it doesn't even belong there.

05:58.733 --> 06:00.735
It's barred on jurisdictional grounds.

06:00.818 --> 06:03.863
My father used to say to me,
"Never accept no for an answer."

06:03.946 --> 06:06.032
Of course, he'd spank me
if I didn't accept it from him.

06:06.115 --> 06:07.992
-Do you spank, Your Honor?
-I jail.

06:08.826 --> 06:11.371
Thirty seconds as to why
I should entertain this lawsuit.

06:11.454 --> 06:15.124
Okay, I realize the jurisdictional
barriers are prohibitive,

06:15.208 --> 06:17.293
but, Your Honor,
we don't let little things like the law

06:17.377 --> 06:18.920
stand in our way in this great country.

06:19.003 --> 06:21.714
The law, for example,
recognizes the Geneva Convention,

06:21.798 --> 06:23.049
but we say the hell with it.

06:23.424 --> 06:26.260
The law has very strict regulations
on domestic wiretapping,

06:26.344 --> 06:27.345
we say the hell with it.

06:27.428 --> 06:29.514
The law says,
if you shoot somebody with a shotgun,

06:29.597 --> 06:32.308
mistaking him for a quail,
you really should call the police.

06:32.392 --> 06:35.269
-Mr. Shore.
-We're cowboys, Judge. We do what we want,

06:35.353 --> 06:37.855
whether it's starting wars,
changing daylight savings time.

06:37.939 --> 06:39.982
We like to play it fast and loose
in this country,

06:40.066 --> 06:41.359
making it up as we go along.

06:41.442 --> 06:42.693
You're not helping yourself.

06:43.069 --> 06:44.946
Your Honor, there's a rumor about you.

06:45.029 --> 06:45.988
Several, actually.

06:46.072 --> 06:47.990
But, the rumor I speak of
is that you give a damn.

06:48.074 --> 06:50.827
That's why I'm here.
If I'm wrong, no hard feelings.

06:50.910 --> 06:51.869
I'm still free for lunch.

06:54.914 --> 06:57.125
I will listen to your client
just to determine

06:57.208 --> 06:59.460
if I'll even accept this case
on jurisdictional grounds.

07:00.044 --> 07:01.379
You're not serious.

07:01.462 --> 07:02.713
Two o'clock. Adjourned.

07:04.257 --> 07:06.426
Don't you be taking
your pants off for her.

07:06.509 --> 07:09.095
-You read my mind.
-I'm serious, Alan.

07:09.178 --> 07:13.349
She's famous for telling lawyers
to drop trou in her chambers.

07:13.433 --> 07:15.476
And more times than not, they do it.

07:16.018 --> 07:18.396
I'll only be dropping trou for you.

07:18.938 --> 07:20.857
You are so sweet.

07:21.732 --> 07:23.609
Are you becoming a romantic, Alan?

07:23.693 --> 07:25.862
Well, now, that you mention it...

07:35.037 --> 07:37.832
(giggles) Oh, my God.

07:39.208 --> 07:41.377
Did you know
yellow roses were my favorite?

07:41.461 --> 07:42.795
I asked around.

07:43.212 --> 07:47.175
Six. You know,
I just lost six yellow roses.

07:47.258 --> 07:48.593
This is perfect.

07:49.385 --> 07:51.637
-I had a dozen in my office...
-Oh.

07:52.430 --> 07:55.016
And six mysteriously disappeared.

07:55.099 --> 07:57.018
-Hmm.
-And wow.

07:57.101 --> 07:59.520
-(chuckles)
-This is fate, I guess.

08:01.105 --> 08:02.523
You're the best.

08:10.573 --> 08:12.408
She's not good for you.

08:12.492 --> 08:14.285
-Why not?
-She just isn't.

08:14.660 --> 08:16.078
A woman knows these things. Trust me.

08:16.746 --> 08:17.830
Denny, you're not a woman.

08:17.914 --> 08:19.499
-Whatever.
-(scoffs)

08:19.582 --> 08:21.083
(sighs) I don't like her.

08:21.959 --> 08:23.503
-You're jealous.
-Not jealous.

08:23.878 --> 08:25.296
-Denny.
-It isn't that.

08:26.422 --> 08:30.635
(sighs) But it's where you'll be going now
for all of your sleepovers.

08:30.718 --> 08:32.178
Not all, I promise.

08:33.513 --> 08:35.640
Don't like you representing
a commie terrorist.

08:35.723 --> 08:38.809
-He's not a terrorist.
-Can't you just once be for this country?

08:38.893 --> 08:41.437
I am for this country.
I love this country.

08:41.521 --> 08:43.523
And can't you just once love George Bush?

08:43.606 --> 08:47.276
Well, that presents a slightly...
bigger challenge.

08:47.360 --> 08:50.071
But I'll tell you what,
invite him to go fishing with us.

08:50.154 --> 08:51.822
-The president?
-Why not?

08:51.906 --> 08:55.076
Well, I doubt he knows how to fish.

08:55.159 --> 08:57.161
Denny, he's leader of the free world.

08:57.245 --> 09:01.457
Surely, he must be capable
of outsmarting a salmon.

09:04.669 --> 09:05.878
No?

09:06.921 --> 09:09.465
I don't want you sleeping with that woman.

09:11.133 --> 09:13.553
And I don't want you attacking my country.

09:16.097 --> 09:17.848
-Stop looking at me.
-Denny.

09:17.932 --> 09:20.101
I know you're looking at me.
I asked you to stop.

09:20.476 --> 09:22.311
-Fine.
-Fine.

09:26.482 --> 09:31.112
Okay, I've thought about it.
And I still have a few questions.

09:32.071 --> 09:33.114
First...

09:35.992 --> 09:37.159
Really, Jerry?

09:37.243 --> 09:39.245
(gasps) Really.

09:40.580 --> 09:43.374
The best times of my life were here.

09:43.708 --> 09:45.835
Which part exactly?

09:45.918 --> 09:48.504
Being ostracized? Turned down for partner?

09:48.588 --> 09:51.632
The arrest for attempted murder?
I realize it was all good.

09:53.301 --> 09:57.054
Most office places,
everybody's mired in their computers

09:57.138 --> 10:00.182
or Blackberries, on their cell phones,
even in the bathrooms.

10:00.558 --> 10:04.604
Most exchanges take place
by e-mail, text message or IM.

10:04.687 --> 10:09.066
It's become such an impersonal universe.

10:09.150 --> 10:10.318
Here...

10:10.943 --> 10:13.529
everyone is so in each other's faces.

10:14.071 --> 10:17.116
I realize now, it's quite magical.

10:17.199 --> 10:19.327
Personally,
I could do with a little less magic.

10:19.660 --> 10:23.581
How joyous that you people
actually know one another.

10:23.664 --> 10:26.000
Could it be any more human?

10:26.083 --> 10:29.086
No matter where you look,
one's got mad cow.

10:29.170 --> 10:32.965
You've got the funny one
who salutes and does push-ups.

10:33.049 --> 10:35.926
There's the transvestite
and the girl who loves him.

10:36.010 --> 10:37.970
A dwarf who comes and goes.

10:38.054 --> 10:40.222
And how to begin to explain... Alan.

10:40.306 --> 10:41.265
(both chuckle)

10:42.516 --> 10:46.437
Certainly,
you can make room for one lawyer

10:46.896 --> 10:50.816
who keeps his hands
on his thighs and purrs.

10:53.944 --> 10:54.987
And then there's you...

10:55.488 --> 10:58.908
who's actually considering
rehiring a man who...

10:59.825 --> 11:02.328
held a serrated cake knife to your throat.

11:03.704 --> 11:06.999
Such compassion for forgiveness.

11:09.001 --> 11:11.170
That makes you the most human of them all.

11:14.006 --> 11:15.299
(sighs)

11:16.592 --> 11:17.718
Okay.

11:19.011 --> 11:20.554
First, that was very good.

11:21.722 --> 11:25.267
Second, it was actually mo... moving.

11:27.895 --> 11:29.855
Let me see
if I can run this up the flagpole.

11:29.939 --> 11:33.818
-Oh!
-It is not a yes yet, Jerry.

11:33.901 --> 11:36.112
But maybe I can cause
some of the others here

11:36.195 --> 11:37.613
to also lose their mind.

11:37.697 --> 11:39.156
-But--
-Thank you, Shirl!

11:39.240 --> 11:41.117
-It's Shirley. You can go now.
-Yeah.

11:47.081 --> 11:48.833
My hopes are so high,

11:48.916 --> 11:51.293
I have to do a higher hop
just to see them.

11:52.128 --> 11:53.295
I know the feeling.

11:57.508 --> 11:58.509
(gasps)

12:05.307 --> 12:06.434
(reporters clamoring)

12:07.143 --> 12:09.854
I'm sorry, I have no comment.
Denny, do you have any comment?

12:09.937 --> 12:11.439
(clamoring continues)

12:11.522 --> 12:14.650
I have nothing
against Guantanamo by the bay.

12:14.734 --> 12:17.236
I happen to like resorts.
And as for suing the country,

12:17.319 --> 12:19.655
well, I think it's wrong,
but the client paid the money.

12:19.739 --> 12:20.781
But let me say this.

12:20.865 --> 12:22.324
In no other country

12:22.408 --> 12:26.036
can you challenge a government
like you can in the US of A.

12:26.120 --> 12:30.374
And that's what freedom's all about,
the right to express unpopular opinions.

12:30.458 --> 12:34.670
Except if you have Arab blood,
then it's straight to Cuba you go.

12:34.754 --> 12:35.880
We're in a war here, guys. Come on.

12:35.963 --> 12:37.465
-REPORTER: Crane!
-Denny Crane.

12:38.340 --> 12:40.843
Did anybody tell you
why you were being arrested?

12:40.926 --> 12:43.888
No. I was grabbed, taken to a cell.

12:44.513 --> 12:46.223
A day later, I was interrogated.

12:46.307 --> 12:50.060
I was able to deduce from the questions
that I was believed to have connections

12:50.144 --> 12:51.771
to either Al-Qaeda or the Taliban.

12:51.854 --> 12:54.398
What evidence did they present
to support this suspicion?

12:54.482 --> 12:57.902
I have never, ever been presented
with any evidence.

12:58.402 --> 13:00.946
Two years later,
after being abused and tortured,

13:01.030 --> 13:02.031
I was released.

13:02.698 --> 13:04.283
There, again, no reason was ever given.

13:04.366 --> 13:07.036
-Did you have a lawyer?
-We were not allowed to have lawyers.

13:08.287 --> 13:11.457
You told them that you had been living
in the United States on a visa

13:11.540 --> 13:13.375
while attending Harvard University?

13:14.418 --> 13:15.586
They were not impressed.

13:16.420 --> 13:19.924
Mr. Kallah,
you've stated that you were tortured.

13:22.426 --> 13:23.969
Can you give us an example?

13:26.222 --> 13:27.306
I was beaten.

13:28.766 --> 13:30.309
Repeatedly deprived of sleep.

13:31.519 --> 13:34.271
I was forced to wear a hood over my head.

13:34.855 --> 13:36.273
Sometimes, for days.

13:37.316 --> 13:39.735
(sighs) I was sexually humiliated.

13:40.444 --> 13:41.278
How so?

13:42.947 --> 13:44.281
I'd rather not go into it.

13:47.076 --> 13:48.077
And what else?

13:49.245 --> 13:51.163
I was forced to lie in a fetal position...

13:52.081 --> 13:54.291
my eyes and my mouth duct taped.

13:55.584 --> 13:56.836
The worst part...

13:58.754 --> 14:00.381
was that we felt it was forever.

14:01.340 --> 14:04.301
We were never gonna be released.
We were never gonna get a trial.

14:05.761 --> 14:07.555
One man, Ali--

14:09.515 --> 14:10.474
A friend.

14:11.559 --> 14:12.768
He was arrested with me.

14:15.729 --> 14:17.022
What happened to your friend, sir?

14:19.233 --> 14:20.442
Finally, he couldn't take it.

14:22.152 --> 14:23.237
(sighs)

14:24.488 --> 14:25.447
He hung himself.

14:26.657 --> 14:28.117
ALAN: He committed suicide?

14:28.200 --> 14:31.620
The Pentagon called it
"manipulative, self-injurious behavior,

14:32.329 --> 14:36.292
an act of asymmetric warfare
engaged against the United States."

14:37.751 --> 14:39.086
Was your friend a terrorist?

14:41.463 --> 14:42.798
No, he was a doctor.

14:47.595 --> 14:50.681
-He tried to kill you.
-Not really.

14:50.764 --> 14:54.018
And let's face it,
we did sort of screw him.

14:54.101 --> 14:56.896
No, we denied him partnership,
which is our right.

14:56.979 --> 14:59.481
He pulled a knife, not his right.

14:59.565 --> 15:00.816
Look, I know it's nuts.

15:00.900 --> 15:05.237
But there were mitigating circumstances,
his Asperger's being one.

15:05.613 --> 15:07.323
He's become a pretty good litigator,

15:07.406 --> 15:10.034
and we're about to lose Denise
to maternity any day now.

15:10.117 --> 15:11.493
We could use the help.

15:12.703 --> 15:14.663
Let's just do it on a trial basis,

15:15.080 --> 15:19.251
if for no other reason
than to assuage my conscience.

15:24.423 --> 15:27.760
The charitable organization that you
worked for was based out of Pakistan?

15:28.552 --> 15:30.387
-Yes.
-You're aware that the organization

15:30.471 --> 15:32.264
has been linked to Al-Qaeda?

15:33.015 --> 15:35.267
When you're trying to do aid work
in a Taliban-controlled area,

15:35.351 --> 15:37.269
-deals have to be made.
-As in Al-Qaeda?

15:37.353 --> 15:39.438
The Taliban and Al-Qaeda
saw humanitarian efforts

15:39.521 --> 15:40.773
as part of the US offensive.

15:41.190 --> 15:44.276
We saw hungry kids.
We did what was necessary to feed them.

15:46.445 --> 15:48.364
So, would you describe yourself
as being cooperative

15:48.447 --> 15:51.283
