31:36.644 --> 31:39.480
Many with no evidence,
giving them no trials, no lawyers.

31:39.564 --> 31:40.481
It's laughable.

31:40.565 --> 31:42.025
And then,
when they finally kill themselves,

31:42.108 --> 31:44.193
we call it
"manipulative, self-injurious behavior,

31:44.277 --> 31:46.946
an act of asymmetric warfare
waged against us."

31:47.030 --> 31:49.198
It's all very funny, very funny.

31:49.449 --> 31:52.285
Maybe the only reason
we aren't having a really good laugh

31:52.368 --> 31:55.288
is because the little GTMO tricks
have started popping up close to home.

31:55.371 --> 31:58.333
The recent revelations
of FBI abuses of the Patriot Act,

31:58.416 --> 32:00.001
all those bogus subpoenas

32:00.084 --> 32:02.503
and manufactured evidence
against American citizens.

32:02.587 --> 32:05.089
Maybe it's just ruined
some of the fun of GTMO.

32:06.257 --> 32:09.260
Oh, well. We're in a war!
We all need to lighten up a little.

32:35.954 --> 32:38.039
What are your intentions towards Alan?

32:38.665 --> 32:40.083
Denny, my friendship with Alan

32:40.166 --> 32:42.085
could not now
or ever be a threat to yours.

32:42.585 --> 32:45.129
Not to mention, I'm not going to do
anything to alienate you.

32:45.213 --> 32:47.590
You're senior patient-- Partner!

32:48.466 --> 32:50.093
(purring)

32:51.135 --> 32:55.139
Look, Shirley won't hire me
unless you okay it.

32:56.683 --> 32:57.725
(exhales)

32:59.185 --> 33:00.144
You still got the doll?

33:02.522 --> 33:03.523
Patty?

33:05.149 --> 33:06.776
I want to spend some time with her.

33:07.318 --> 33:09.529
-Forget it!
-I won't do anything untoward.

33:10.071 --> 33:12.115
Dinner? Maybe a movie?

33:13.157 --> 33:15.994
I give you my word, I will not touch her.

33:16.077 --> 33:18.121
No offense, but your word...

33:18.204 --> 33:20.498
I'll give you something of mine
that I hold dear.

33:23.001 --> 33:23.835
Please.

33:25.545 --> 33:27.130
Jerry, my new friend.

33:30.383 --> 33:31.217
One night.

33:32.969 --> 33:34.345
Welcome back to the team, son.

33:35.638 --> 33:36.472
Are you serious?

33:38.182 --> 33:39.809
-Truth is I've missed you.
-Oh!

33:40.601 --> 33:42.145
Thank you! (wheezes)

33:42.937 --> 33:45.189
Give me one of them little hops
on your way out.

33:45.273 --> 33:46.774
Thank you! Thank you!

33:46.858 --> 33:48.109
("'Til Your Fool Comes Home" playing)

33:48.192 --> 33:52.030
<i>♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah ♪</i>

33:58.369 --> 34:00.079
FOLGER: They say, when people get scared,

34:00.163 --> 34:03.624
the first thing they'll give up
is their civil liberties.

34:03.708 --> 34:05.334
That's why, after 9/11,

34:05.418 --> 34:08.421
we were only too happy
to get frisked at airports.

34:08.504 --> 34:10.631
Some of us enjoyed it more than others.

34:11.507 --> 34:15.053
But when it gets to a point
where people are captured...

34:15.762 --> 34:16.804
then tortured...

34:17.430 --> 34:19.182
not because there is evidence,

34:19.265 --> 34:22.894
but rather,
just to see if there's evidence,

34:22.977 --> 34:26.814
when they are jailed in perpetuity,
afforded no trial,

34:26.898 --> 34:29.776
my God, the court has a duty to step in.

34:30.818 --> 34:33.362
The government's motion
to dismiss is denied.

34:34.405 --> 34:37.408
-(people chattering)
-(sighs) Oh, my.

34:40.995 --> 34:43.790
-Thank you, Mr. Shore.
-Thank you, Benyam.

34:43.873 --> 34:47.126
I wouldn't expect a jury to give you much.
I'd recommend settling.

34:47.210 --> 34:49.712
Not to mention,
this will probably be appealed.

34:49.962 --> 34:51.464
Yes, thank you so much.

34:53.341 --> 34:55.134
Uh, where's Mr. Crane?

34:57.678 --> 34:58.638
Oh, dear.

34:59.263 --> 35:00.431
Why are you here?

35:01.265 --> 35:03.226
I just wanted to salute your ruling.

35:04.310 --> 35:06.437
-Very ballsy.
-Thank you.

35:07.146 --> 35:07.980
You can go.

35:09.232 --> 35:10.566
-Anything else?
-No.

35:12.819 --> 35:14.237
-Nothing else at all?
-Nope.

35:14.320 --> 35:16.405
-Because if there is--
-Mr. Crane,

35:16.489 --> 35:17.740
please leave my chambers.

35:20.118 --> 35:21.035
Yes.

35:24.705 --> 35:25.540
Thank you.

35:34.382 --> 35:35.758
I forgot my briefcase.

35:38.886 --> 35:43.558
I just wanted to congratulate
you again on the ruling.

35:44.308 --> 35:45.226
Ballsy.

35:45.810 --> 35:46.644
Thank you.

36:03.077 --> 36:04.328
(elevator dings)

36:04.412 --> 36:08.708
So, Hands Espenson is officially back.

36:09.792 --> 36:11.419
I did a little checking.

36:11.502 --> 36:15.006
He's become an excellent litigator
and a solid citizen.

36:15.756 --> 36:16.674
We hope.

36:20.845 --> 36:22.805
Shirley, Paul, have a nice evening.

36:31.689 --> 36:33.274
-(knock on door)
-(door opens)

36:33.357 --> 36:34.734
Glor-- Oh.

36:34.817 --> 36:35.651
Alan.

36:37.153 --> 36:38.154
(chuckles)

36:40.031 --> 36:44.243
I'm new at this, uh, relationship game.

36:45.286 --> 36:47.371
And not so much new, I guess, as, uh...

36:47.455 --> 36:48.664
Rusty.

36:49.749 --> 36:51.667
Just so I'm clear.

36:52.335 --> 36:54.337
If I'm ever even...

36:55.296 --> 36:58.007
slightly attracted to another woman,

36:58.090 --> 36:59.675
I should just lie about that?

36:59.759 --> 37:02.094
-Through your teeth.
-Hmm.

37:03.930 --> 37:08.601
Really? Why would you tolerate
dishonesty from your partner?

37:08.684 --> 37:09.644
I wouldn't.

37:09.977 --> 37:12.897
If I ever catch you lying to me,
it's over.

37:13.439 --> 37:15.149
-Uh, but you just--
-No.

37:15.650 --> 37:17.193
It's very simple, Alan.

37:17.276 --> 37:20.988
When you tell me that you're not attracted
to anybody else but me...

37:22.448 --> 37:23.950
it needs to be the truth.

37:40.925 --> 37:43.427
I forgot how much they can befuddle you.

37:43.511 --> 37:45.763
Alan, would you listen to me
when it comes to women?

37:45.846 --> 37:48.266
-Can you do that, please?
-Why should I trust you?

37:48.349 --> 37:49.517
You're jealous of her.

37:49.600 --> 37:50.851
You'd be glad if it ended.

37:50.935 --> 37:54.146
-I'm not jealous of her anymore.
-You're jealous of Jerry.

37:54.230 --> 37:58.192
Well, women, I can compete against.
Other men...

37:59.193 --> 38:02.613
Let's face it.
You go for the soft, sensitive type.

38:02.697 --> 38:03.739
It's why I fell for you.

38:05.408 --> 38:09.996
Why are relationships with women
so much more complicated?

38:10.079 --> 38:12.123
Oh, women. Come on, Alan.

38:12.206 --> 38:14.542
Women have this hormone thing.

38:15.042 --> 38:20.089
Much as I love 'em, they're unstable,
which is why they can never be president.

38:20.172 --> 38:22.049
You don't think a woman
should ever be president?

38:22.133 --> 38:24.719
Oh, come on. Do you? In time of war?

38:24.802 --> 38:27.930
How would a woman handle a 9/11?
She'd cry.

38:28.014 --> 38:29.557
You think Hillary Clinton
would have cried?

38:29.640 --> 38:31.767
Well, uh, maybe not Hillary.

38:31.851 --> 38:33.936
-(chuckles)
-But she has a few chromosome issues.

38:34.020 --> 38:35.730
-Let's face it.
-What are you talking about?

38:35.813 --> 38:40.234
Alan, don't you ever look at her at times
and think, that's a guy?

38:40.318 --> 38:42.361
No, I find her...

38:42.445 --> 38:46.407
sexy in a "praying mantis
in a knee-length skirt" kind of way.

38:46.490 --> 38:47.992
You ever mentally undress her?

38:49.410 --> 38:51.954
(chuckling) I was talking
about my relationship issues.

38:52.413 --> 38:55.041
How did we get to mentally
undressing Hillary Clinton?

38:55.124 --> 38:58.252
-And so quickly, I might add.
-Because it's all related!

38:58.336 --> 38:59.920
I'm gonna tell you something
right here and now

39:00.004 --> 39:02.006
about women and a relationship.

39:02.089 --> 39:06.886
We would never be in Guantanamo
if it weren't for Hillary Clinton.

39:08.554 --> 39:11.974
I know the reason's obvious,
but give it to me just the same.

39:16.145 --> 39:19.231
Bill Clinton would never have lied
in the deposition.

39:19.315 --> 39:21.400
He wouldn't have risked impeachment.

39:21.484 --> 39:23.944
So, what if a sexual indiscretion
came to light?

39:24.028 --> 39:25.488
The public would have forgiven him.

39:25.571 --> 39:28.282
-But, Hillary...
-(scoffs)

39:28.366 --> 39:32.953
The reason he lied is because
he was afraid Hillary would find out.

39:33.037 --> 39:35.915
That's why he was impeached.
That's why Al Gore didn't win.

39:36.665 --> 39:39.168
And after all that
impeachment scandal crap,

39:39.251 --> 39:41.003
the public would've elected any fool...

39:41.087 --> 39:43.047
-(laughs)
-...other than a Democrat.

39:43.130 --> 39:45.174
-Cut to...
-(scoffs) George W.

39:45.257 --> 39:47.593
All because of a woman scorned.

39:48.844 --> 39:50.554
And... they're unstable.

39:50.638 --> 39:52.515
-All women?
-Every single one of 'em.

39:52.598 --> 39:54.433
-All shapes and sizes?
-Oh, the fat, the thin,

39:54.517 --> 39:55.726
the big, and the s...

39:59.063 --> 40:00.439
Oh, for God sakes.

40:00.523 --> 40:01.607
(exhales)

40:03.901 --> 40:05.444
All right, don't tell me.

40:05.778 --> 40:10.408
"Denny, I never want to see you again."

40:14.870 --> 40:16.122
(groans)

40:17.581 --> 40:20.042
The little ones are the most unstable.
Women.

40:21.127 --> 40:23.796
-Can't live with them.
-Can't take 'em quail hunting.

40:23.879 --> 40:24.922
Alan, you're best off with me.

40:25.464 --> 40:27.967
-I'm rock steady.
-Yes, you are.

40:28.050 --> 40:30.678
-Uncomplicated.
-Couldn't be simpler.

40:30.761 --> 40:31.846
Denny Crane.

40:32.471 --> 40:33.431
Denny Crane.

40:35.433 --> 40:36.559
(chuckles)

40:36.642 --> 40:38.310
(blues music plays)

40:53.117 --> 40:54.368
NARRATOR:<i> Next on</i> Boston Legal...

40:54.452 --> 40:56.954
Please do not tell me
that you've stolen the Stanley Cup.

40:57.037 --> 40:59.582
My name belongs on this cup.

40:59.665 --> 41:00.958
But you've never won it.

41:01.041 --> 41:02.793
DENNY:
I love it when the bride's knocked up.

41:02.877 --> 41:03.878
Everybody gossips.

41:03.961 --> 41:06.005
(yelling)

41:06.088 --> 41:07.756
-The head is coming!
-Oh, my God!

41:07.840 --> 41:10.301
You have about a half a minute
to tell me what's going on

41:10.384 --> 41:12.052
before those agents knock this door down.

41:12.136 --> 41:13.596
This is Maria and her son, Alberto.

41:13.679 --> 41:16.140
Maria's undocumented.
The church offered them sanctuary.

41:16.223 --> 41:18.976
This behavior will not be tolerated.

41:19.059 --> 41:20.394
I will fire you.

41:20.478 --> 41:21.562
There it is.

41:25.274 --> 41:26.984
(theme music playing)
